Poetry Package Management

Manage dependencies in your Python project with [bold cyan]poetry[/bold cyan].

[dim]# Adding dependencies[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry add[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow]               [dim]# Add package to dependencies[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry add[/bold] [yellow]package1 package2[/yellow]    [dim]# Add multiple packages[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry add -D[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow]            [dim]# Add to dev dependencies[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry add[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow][bold]@[/bold][yellow]^2.0[/yellow]       [dim]# Add with version constraint[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry add[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow][bold]@[/bold][yellow]latest[/yellow]    [dim]# Add latest version[/dim]

[dim]# Removing dependencies[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry remove[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow]            [dim]# Remove package[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry remove -D[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow]         [dim]# Remove dev dependency[/dim]

[dim]# Updating dependencies[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry update[/bold]                      [dim]# Update all dependencies[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry update[/bold] [yellow]package[/yellow]            [dim]# Update specific package[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry update[/bold] [yellow]package1 package2[/yellow] [dim]# Update multiple packages[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry lock[/bold]                        [dim]# Update poetry.lock without installing[/dim]
[bold green]$[/bold green] [bold]poetry lock --no-update[/bold]            [dim]# Refresh lock file without updating versions[/dim]

[bold]Version constraints:[/bold]
[cyan]^2.0[/cyan] - Compatible (>=2.0.0, <3.0.0)  [cyan]~2.1[/cyan] - Approximately (>=2.1.0, <2.2.0)
[cyan]>=2.0,<3.0[/cyan] - Range  [cyan]2.1.3[/cyan] - Exact version
